<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="405" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">
This species is named in honor of the well-known Russian entomologist, an expert of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cameron, 1881" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sierola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraOrder="Aculeata" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="infraOrder">Aculeata</taxonomicName>
, Professor Arkady S. Lelej for celebrating his 75-anniversary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="405" type="host">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">Host.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">
Larvae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kusnezov" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Haplochrois" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplochrois theae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="405">Haplochrois theae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kusnezov, 1916).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="405" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">Distribution.</paragraph>
