</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="405" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="405">
This species is similar to the species 
<taxonomicName authority="Cameron, 1881" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1881" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sierola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sierola shimotsukeana" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shimotsukeana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="405">Sierola shimotsukeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Terayama, 2006 for the shape of head. But it can be distinguished by having 1M2c nearly rectangular, metapostnotal-propodeal disc coriaceous, and mandible light castaneous while 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="S." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="S. shimotsukeana" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shimotsukeana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="405">S. shimotsukeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having 1M2c oval, posterior area of metapostnotal-propodeal disc smooth medially, and mandible black.
</paragraph>
